      • getIcon

        public javax.swing.Icon getIcon()
        Returns an Icon used to indicate the value in the accordion. Implementations may return null to indicate that the node should display no icon. The default implementation returns null.
        Returns:
        an Icon that represents the node or null

      • getAncillaryIcon

        public javax.swing.Icon getAncillaryIcon()
        Returns an alternate Icon placed at the right side of the accordion node. Implementations may return null to indicate that the node should display no such ancillary indicator. The default implementation returns null.
        Returns:
        an Icon to display at the right side of the node

      • getToolTip

        public java.lang.String getToolTip()
        Returns a tooltip to be displayed on the value's node. Implementations may return null to prevent displaying a tooltip. The default implementation returns null
        Returns:
        a tooltip or null

      • getClassification
